From Carl Christensen Subject Re Asimov stamp Laurence Gene Battin writes Apart from the suggestion that appeared in the letters column of Skeptical Inquirer recently has there been any further mention about a possible Asimov commemorative stamp If this idea hasn't been followed up does anyone know what needs to be done to get this to happen I think that its a great Should we start a petition or something I believe that there's a year period from time of death until a person can be on a commemorative It was broken once for Lyndon Johnson I think but other than that it has held for Of course we can still start now the Elvis stamp was petitioned for ages and things really moved once it got past the year anniversary of his Carl Christensen of Computer Science Temple University Curiouser and curiouser LC Philadelphia PA USA